The article discusses the violent assault on American democracy that occurred on January 6th, 2021, when insurrectionists invaded the United States Capitol in an attempt to overturn the election results. It highlights the bravery of law enforcement officers and the resolve of the people's representatives in defending democracy. The article emphasizes that Americans from all political affiliations have come together to defend freedom, liberty, and the rule of law. The author, as President of the Senate and a former Senator, acknowledges the heroism of law enforcement officers and expresses condolences for those who lost their lives protecting democracy. The article concludes by urging readers to continue the fight to safeguard and strengthen democracy for future generations.